ed them to speak ? </div><div class="t ma2 x5b h2d y1c38 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t ma1d x3f h2d y1c38 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Could they thus speak at will? </div><div class="t me58 x29 h2d y131 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">III. Questions on Heb. 1 :1, 2. </div><div class="t m988 x5b h2d yc28 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t me2 x3f h2d yc28 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Who has spoken in time past? </div><div class="t m127 x5b h2d y19 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t ma1e x3f h2d y6ac ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Has he spoken frequently? </div><div class="t m2b6 x5b h2d y368 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m14c1 x3f h2d y1981 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Through whom has he spoken? </div><div class="t ma2 x5b h2d y18b9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m77a x3f h2d y1728 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Who speaks in the last days? </div><div class="t m1cd x5b h2d yb4b ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m77e x3f h2d y1925 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Through whom? </div><div class="t m1d0 x5b h2d y19be ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t ma9e x3f h2d y19be ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Who, then, is the speaker, both in time past and </div><div class="t ma3b x6d h2d yea ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in these last days? </div><div class="t m1d2 x5b h2d y139 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t m571 x3f h2d y139 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Have we, then, any authority for discriminating </div><div class="t me71 x13 h2d y198c ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">between the Old and New Testament, and saying </div><div class="t m3e5 x13 h2d y1905 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that one is of more importance than the other? </div><div class="t m254 x1d h2d y161d ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTES. </div><div class="t m1461 x60 h15 y381 ff4 fs1 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. THE </div><div class="t m289 xf h2d y381 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Holy Scriptures which Timothy had known </div><div class="t maf7 x64 h2d y698 ff4 fsa fc